value.title: Kid Rock performs at Trump rally in Michigan, announces 'one last monster tour' coming
value.excerpt: On a night that felt like a late-summer concert, Kid Rock joined Donald Trump Jr. and supporters of the president at a campaign rally east of Detroit.

value.title: Trump HHS spokesperson Michael Caputo deletes Twitter account after late-night rant
value.excerpt: The top spokesperson for the Department of Health and Human Services deleted his Twitter in the aftermath of a late-night rant in which he suggested tear gassing journalists and battled with other users on the social media platform.

value.title: Biden proposes $5 trillion in new spending, undaunted by Trump's massive deficits
value.excerpt: The nation's deficits and outlays have hit post-World War II highs thanks to tax cuts under President Donald Trump, but Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden is proposing adding to that, at least in the near term, with a $5.4 trillion spending plan.

value.title: Amy Poehler and Maya Rudolph Help Kamala Harris Fundraiser Raise $6 Million
value.excerpt: Amy Poehler and Maya Rudolph hosted a “grassroots” fundraiser on Monday, along with Kamala Harris and Hillary Clinton, that raised more than $6 million for the Democratic ticket.

value.title: Down-ballot Dems split from Biden on door-knocking
value.excerpt: Amid growing anxiety about the loss of a valuable election-year tool, an increasing number of Democrats are ignoring Joe Biden’s lead and resuming traditional door-to-door canvassing.

value.title: Lt. Col. Vindman says he now identifies as a 'Never Trumper'
value.excerpt: Lt. Col. Alexander Vindman says he now identifies as a "Never Trumper" following his official retirement from the military.

value.title: Trump baselessly questions climate science during California wildfire briefing
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Monday baselessly asserted that climate change is not playing a role in the catastrophic wildfires overtaking forests across the west, rebutting an official briefing him who pleaded for the President listen to the science.

value.title: Republicans see Trump's rallies as his path to victory. Democrats welcome the events.
value.excerpt: The decision to hold a political rally has become one of the sharpest differences between the candidates in an election year defined by a global pandemic.

value.title: Trump alma mater says Biden plan would lead to more economic growth
value.excerpt: Biden and Trump would both increase federal debt, but Democrat would boost wage growth and lower health costs.

value.title: Biden calls Trump a ‘climate arsonist’ who ‘won’t take responsibility’ for wildfires
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden accused President Trump of being “a climate arsonist” and charged that if the president wins another four years in the White House, the wildfires raging in the western U.S. will become more “devastating and more deadly.”

value.title: Trump awards Distinguished Flying Cross to 7 California National Guard members
value.excerpt: President Trump on Monday awarded the Distinguished Flying Cross to seven members of the California National Guard who helped rescue over 200 people earlier this month from the massive wildfire.

value.title: Chaffetz blasts Biden for climate change Trump attack: former VP 'had his chance and he blew it'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden's attack on President Trump Monday was tone-deaf, former House Oversight Committee Chairman Jason Chaffetz told “Outnumbered Overtime” on Monday, after the former vice president took aim from Delaware at President Trump’s climate change “denial.”

value.title: Trump and Biden both boast about creating auto industry jobs — but differ on how
value.excerpt: "I got you so many damn car plants,” President Trump told auto workers last week. Biden, meanwhile, is pledging "1 million new, well-paying jobs in the American automobile industry."

value.excerpt: "They want to play war — this is war," Stone remarked as he stirred baseless fears of electoral fraud and urged President Donald Trump to seize power.

value.title: Fact check: Trump makes four false claims in one sentence
value.excerpt: In what may be a new record for President Donald Trump, he made four false claims in one sentence of a tweet on Saturday.

value.title: Trump says 'football is boring as hell' at Nevada rally, continuing his grievance against racial injustice protests
value.excerpt: At a weekend rally in Nevada, the president continued his attacks on NFL players who protest racial injustice and police brutality on the field.

value.title: Court rules that Trump can end humanitarian protections for 300,000 immigrants
value.excerpt: A split federal appeals court panel said the Trump administration can terminate humanitarian protections for 300,000 immigrants from Sudan, Nicaragua, Haiti and El Salvador.

value.title: Trump campaign returns to economy with 8-figure ad buy, calls it ‘defining issue in this race’
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign is set to release a mid-eight-figure ad buy Tuesday touting the economy during President Trump's first term after a recent emphasis on "law and order" messaging, saying the economy is the "defining issue" of the 2020 presidential race, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Joe Biden says US is facing 'one of the most difficult moments in our history'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden said Monday that the United States is facing one of the most difficult moments in the nation's history, with "four historic crises all at the same time."

value.title: Race tightening but Biden remains on top 50 days out from election
value.excerpt: With 50 days to go until Election Day on Nov. 3, it still appears to be Joe Biden’s race to lose. But the contest between the Democratic presidential nominee and President Trump has tightened over the past month.

value.title: How For-Profit Colleges Might Fare Under Joe Biden And Kamala Harris
value.excerpt: For-profit colleges have had it made the last few years. After years of scrutiny and tougher regulation, many for-profit executives made a sigh of relief when Trump—the owner of an unaccredited for-profit college—was elected.
